From ff0533236c2ad7f9f248c21a1bfe16e4dafb7a34 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude Fleet <fleet@factorylm.local>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 10:25:32 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] fix(tools): route demo_plc_poller through the one-pipeline
 ingest contract

The poller's embedded SCHEMA_DDL/live_signal_cache DDL never matched the
deployed Hub schema (migrations 020/033/036), and its direct NeonDB
INSERT/UPSERT was a second, rival persistence path in violation of
.claude/rules/one-pipeline-ingest.md.

Instead of patching the DDL to match the deployed shape, remove the
poller's DB writes entirely and route through mira-relay's canonical
contract: build_tag_entry/build_ingest_batch (mira-relay/ingest_contract.py,
loaded by file path like simlab/publishers.py::RelayIngestPublisher) ->
POST /api/v1/tags/ingest. The relay's tag_ingest.ingest_batch remains the
only NeonDB writer (tag_events + live_signal_cache).

Adds --relay-hmac-key for the production-shaped HMAC auth path (mirrors
RelayIngestPublisher); drops --db-url and psycopg entirely.

Updates docs/known-issues.md to mark the stale-schema issue fixed.
